The family of Anni Dewani who was murdered while on honeymoon in South Africa, brother, Ashish Hindocha (L), father Vinod Hindocha (2-L) Mother Nilam Hindocha (2-R) and Sister Ami Denborg (R) leave Westminster Crown Court July 24, 2013. JOHANNESBURG - Anni Dewani's family has expressed shock at the decision to grant parole to her killer Zola Tongo. He will be a free man from June, subject to several conditions. Tongo was sentenced to 18-years in prison after he pleaded guilty to murdering Anni Dewani while she was on honeymoon in South Africa in 2010. READ:Â Anni Dewani's killer granted parole Tongo confessed to receiving R15,000 from Dewani's husband Shrien. He alleged that Shrien gave him the money to hire hitmen to kill Anni. Anni's family says the decision confirms that South Africa doesn't want to reduce crime, but rather encourage it.